‘Representation of Christmas Tree’
2022, bouquets. ❄️💀
Chrysanthemum, glaucous cedar, spruce, tulip, carnation, arbutus, lavender, brachyglottis, berggarten sage, rhododendron, hawthorn, statice, gypsophalia.
•
Some faves return again this year including the variegated rhodi and traditional small army of jumping spiders (hello lords a leaping??), along with some new forage scores of precious tiny needled oriental spruce that smells like heaven, the one Arbutus by the pickleball courts that’s always going off, and some very assertive hawthorn because there’s so much beauty in ouvertly adapting to protect yourself. 🎄🌿

•
•
•
There have been thoughts rattling around in my brain for a long time that I can't seem to solidify into an articulate paragraph about why I feel like the increased compartmentalization of our personalities and hobbies and pets into separate media profiles is... dangerous? Problematic, certainly. Particularly for women who are historically socialized to make ourselves small and easily digestible, it feels like a huge disservice to the depth of ourselves to allow people to believe in any one shallow attribute they'd choose to consume in isolation from the context that is any jumbled slop pile of existing.
With understanding that there are good and deeply individual reasons to portion things, let's also stay away from words like 'vulnerability' and 'authentic' (ick!) to acknowledge that yes, whatever portions we wish can remain private, which is all together included in the terror and chaos of being vast and inscrutably human.
Brought to you by the recurring existential crisis of why to share, of being perceived, of being known, the hyper awareness of my own juxtaposed overlapping audience and realizing just now that it's good to remember they're responsible for signing themselves up to view the whole realistic mess, and to keep on doing my weird br4nd where I apparently can mange to write out something coherent and eloquent and use the word 'slop' all at the same time.

#whereami
#whatdayisit

‘Representation of Christmas Tree’
2023, bouquets. 🪶💀

Erica carnea, chrysanthemum, ranunculus, rose, lavender, scotch pine, CA bay, hebe, Rhododendron ponticum, waxflower, gypsophalia, Thuja plicata. 

I went a little off the rails in terms of volume - ten pieces including three hand bouquets and a hair adornment. 😵‍💫
The Erica is the star of the show for me but guess who found an Umbellularia californica growing in the neighborhood. 👀
